# Rancher Manager MCP Server

This is a Model Context Protocol (MCP) server for Rancher Manager API with stdio and HTTP transport support.

## Key Files
- `cmd/main.go` - Main entry point for the MCP server
- `internal/server/server.go` - Server implementation and tool registration
- `internal/server/rancher_client.go` - Rancher API client
- `internal/mcp/server.go` - MCP protocol implementation

## Development
- Use environment variables for tokens (see `.env.example`)
- Never commit tokens or secrets to git
- The server supports both stdio (default) and HTTP transports
- Tools are registered in `registerTools()` method

## API
- Uses Rancher Manager Kubernetes API: `/apis/management.cattle.io/v3/`
- Authentication via Bearer token in Authorization header
- Reference: https://ranchermanager.docs.rancher.com/api/api-reference
